      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Asq borrows the formatting conventions of the Ruby Date object. Below is a summary of the most commonly needed conversions, for more information please see the <a href="http://ruby-doc.org/stdlib-2.2.3/libdoc/date/rdoc/Date.html#method-i-strftime">Date documentation</a>.</p>

        <p><b>NOTE:</b>By default, Asq will use today's date when filling out variables. If you would like to use yesterday's date, use a preceding 'y#' in the filename. Don't worry, it will get stripped out of the delivered filename. <i>ex. "y#time_warner_%Y%m%d.csv"</i></p>

        <p>The directive consists of a percent (%) character,
        zero or more flags, optional minimum field width,
        optional modifier and a conversion specifier
        as follows.<br>
          <code>%&lt;flags&gt;&lt;width&gt;&lt;modifier&gt;&lt;conversion&gt;</code>
        </p>

        <p>
          <b>Flags:</b><br>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-  don't pad a numerical output.</li>
            <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;_  use spaces for padding.</li>
            <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;0  use zeros for padding.</li>
            <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;^  upcase the result string.</li>
            <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#  change case.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <p><b>Format directives:</b></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Date (Year, Month, Day):
            <ul>
              <li>%Y - Year with century (ex: 2015)</li>
              <li>%y - year % 100 (00..99)</li>
              <li>%m - Month of the year, zero-padded (01..12)<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%-m  no-padded (1..12)</li>
              <li>%B - The full month name ('January)<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%^B  uppercased ('JANUARY')</li>
              <li>%b - The abbreviated month name ('Jan')<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%^b  uppercased ('JAN)</li>
              <li>%d - Day of the month, zero-padded (01..31)<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%-d  no-padded (1..31)</li>
              <li>%j - Day of the year (001..366)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>Weekday:
            <ul>
              <li>%A - The full weekday name ('Sunday)<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%^A  uppercased ('SUNDAY')</li>
              <li>%a - The abbreviated name ('Sun')<br>
                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;%^a  uppercased ('SUN)</li>
              <li>%u - Day of the week (Monday is 1, 1..7)</li>
              <li>%w - Day of the week (Sunday is 0, 0..6)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
